028/**
029 * Describes a single operation parameter.
030 *
031 * <p>
032 * The Parameter Object describes a single parameter used in a Swagger 2.0 API operation. A unique parameter is 
033 * defined by a combination of a name and location (in). Parameters can be passed in various locations including 
034 * the path, query string, headers, body, or form data.
035 *
036 * <h5 class='section'>Swagger Specification:</h5>
037 * <p>
038 * The Parameter Object supports the following fields:
039 * <ul class='spaced-list'>
040 *    <li><c>name</c> (string, REQUIRED) - The name of the parameter
041 *    <li><c>in</c> (string, REQUIRED) - The location of the parameter. Possible values: <js>"path"</js>, <js>"query"</js>, <js>"header"</js>, <js>"body"</js>, or <js>"formData"</js>
042 *    <li><c>description</c> (string) - A brief description of the parameter
043 *    <li><c>required</c> (boolean) - Determines whether this parameter is mandatory (must be <jk>true</jk> if <c>in</c> is <js>"path"</js>)
044 *    <li><c>schema</c> ({@link SchemaInfo}) - The schema defining the type used for the body parameter (only if <c>in</c> is <js>"body"</js>)
045 *    <li><c>type</c> (string) - The type of the parameter (for non-body parameters). Values: <js>"string"</js>, <js>"number"</js>, <js>"integer"</js>, <js>"boolean"</js>, <js>"array"</js>, <js>"file"</js>
046 *    <li><c>format</c> (string) - The format modifier (e.g., <js>"int32"</js>, <js>"int64"</js>, <js>"float"</js>, <js>"double"</js>, <js>"date"</js>, <js>"date-time"</js>)
047 *    <li><c>allowEmptyValue</c> (boolean) - Sets the ability to pass empty-valued parameters (valid only for <js>"query"</js> or <js>"formData"</js> parameters)
048 *    <li><c>items</c> ({@link Items}) - Required if type is <js>"array"</js>. Describes the type of items in the array
049 *    <li><c>collectionFormat</c> (string) - How multiple values are formatted. Values: <js>"csv"</js>, <js>"ssv"</js>, <js>"tsv"</js>, <js>"pipes"</js>, <js>"multi"</js>
050 *    <li><c>default</c> (any) - The default value
051 *    <li><c>maximum</c> (number), <c>exclusiveMaximum</c> (boolean), <c>minimum</c> (number), <c>exclusiveMinimum</c> (boolean) - Numeric constraints
052 *    <li><c>maxLength</c> (integer), <c>minLength</c> (integer), <c>pattern</c> (string) - String constraints
053 *    <li><c>maxItems</c> (integer), <c>minItems</c> (integer), <c>uniqueItems</c> (boolean) - Array constraints
054 *    <li><c>enum</c> (array) - Possible values for this parameter
055 *    <li><c>multipleOf</c> (number) - Must be a multiple of this value
056 * </ul>
057 *
058 * <p>
059 * There are five possible parameter types (determined by the <c>in</c> field):
060 * <ul class='spaced-list'>
061 *    <li><js>"path"</js> - Used together with Path Templating, where the parameter value is actually part of the
062 *       operation's URL.
063 *       This does not include the host or base path of the API.
064 *       For example, in <c>/items/{itemId}</c>, the path parameter is <c>itemId</c>.
065 *    <li><js>"query"</js> - Parameters that are appended to the URL.
066 *       For example, in <c>/items?id=###</c>, the query parameter is <c>id</c>.
067 *    <li><js>"header"</js> - Custom headers that are expected as part of the request.
068 *    <li><js>"body"</js> - The payload that's appended to the HTTP request.
069 *       Since there can only be one payload, there can only be one body parameter.
070 *       The name of the body parameter has no effect on the parameter itself and is used for documentation purposes
071 *       only.
072 *       Since Form parameters are also in the payload, body and form parameters cannot exist together for the same
073 *       operation.
074 *    <li><js>"formData"</js> - Used to describe the payload of an HTTP request when either
075 *       <c>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</c>, <c>multipart/form-data</c> or both are used as the
076 *       content type of the request (in Swagger's definition, the consumes property of an operation).
077 *       This is the only parameter type that can be used to send files, thus supporting the file type.
078 *       Since form parameters are sent in the payload, they cannot be declared together with a body parameter for the
079 *       same operation.
080 *       Form parameters have a different format based on the content-type used (for further details, consult
081 *       <c>http://www.w3.org/TR/html401/interact/forms.html#h-17.13.4</c>):
082 *       <ul>
083 *          <li><js>"application/x-www-form-urlencoded"</js> - Similar to the format of Query parameters but as a
084 *             payload.
085 *             For example, <c>foo=1&amp;bar=swagger</c> - both <c>foo</c> and <c>bar</c> are form
086 *             parameters.
087 *             This is normally used for simple parameters that are being transferred.
088 *          <li><js>"multipart/form-data"</js> - each parameter takes a section in the payload with an internal header.
089 *             For example, for the header <c>Content-Disposition: form-data; name="submit-name"</c> the name of
090 *             the parameter is <c>submit-name</c>.
091 *             This type of form parameters is more commonly used for file transfers.
092 *       </ul>
093 *    </li>
094 * </ul>
095 *
096 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
097 * <p class='bjava'>
098 *    <jc>// Construct using SwaggerBuilder.</jc>
099 *    ParameterInfo <jv>info</jv> = <jsm>parameterInfo</jsm>(<js>"query"</js>, <js>"foo"</js>);
100 *
101 *    <jc>// Serialize using JsonSerializer.</jc>
102 *    String <jv>json</jv> = Json.<jsm>from</jsm>(<jv>info</jv>);
103 *
104 *    <jc>// Or just use toString() which does the same as above.</jc>
105 *    <jv>json</jv> = <jv>info</jv>.toString();
106 * </p>
107 * <p class='bjson'>
108 *    <jc>// Output</jc>
109 *    {
110 *       <js>"in"</js>: <js>"query"</js>,
111 *       <js>"name"</js>: <js>"foo"</js>
112 *    }
113 * </p>
114 *
115 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
116 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/specification/v2/#parameter-object">Swagger 2.0 Specification &gt; Parameter Object</a>
117 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://swagger.io/docs/specification/2-0/describing-parameters/">Swagger Describing Parameters</a>
118 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanSwagger2">juneau-bean-swagger-v2</a>
119 * </ul>
120 */
121public class ParameterInfo extends SwaggerElement {
122
123   private static final String[] VALID_IN = {"query", "header", "path", "formData", "body"};
124   private static final String[] VALID_TYPES = {"string", "number", "integer", "boolean", "array", "file"};
125   private static final String[] VALID_COLLECTION_FORMATS = {"csv", "ssv", "tsv", "pipes", "multi"};
126

128      name,
129      in,
130      description,
131      type,
132      format,
133      pattern,

138      multipleOf;
139   private Integer
140      maxLength,
141      minLength,
142      maxItems,
143      minItems;
144   private Boolean
145      required,
146      allowEmptyValue,
147      exclusiveMaximum,
148      exclusiveMinimum,
149      uniqueItems;
150   private SchemaInfo schema;
151   private Items items;
152   private Object _default;  // NOSONAR - Intentional naming.
153   private Set<Object> _enum;  // NOSONAR - Intentional naming.
154   private Object example;
155   private Map<String,String> examples;

157   /**
158    * Default constructor.
159    */
160   public ParameterInfo() {}
161
162   /**
163    * Copy constructor.
164    *
165    * @param copyFrom The object to copy.
166    */
167   public ParameterInfo(ParameterInfo copyFrom) {
168      super(copyFrom);
169
170      this.allowEmptyValue = copyFrom.allowEmptyValue;
171      this.collectionFormat = copyFrom.collectionFormat;
172      this._default = copyFrom._default;
173      this.description = copyFrom.description;
174      this._enum = copyOf(copyFrom._enum);
175      this.example = copyFrom.example;
176      this.exclusiveMaximum = copyFrom.exclusiveMaximum;
177      this.exclusiveMinimum = copyFrom.exclusiveMinimum;
178      this.format = copyFrom.format;
179      this.in = copyFrom.in;
180      this.items = copyFrom.items == null ? null : copyFrom.items.copy();
181      this.maximum = copyFrom.maximum;
182      this.maxItems = copyFrom.maxItems;
183      this.maxLength = copyFrom.maxLength;
184      this.minimum = copyFrom.minimum;
185      this.minItems = copyFrom.minItems;
186      this.minLength = copyFrom.minLength;
187      this.multipleOf = copyFrom.multipleOf;
188      this.name = copyFrom.name;
189      this.pattern = copyFrom.pattern;
190      this.required = copyFrom.required;
191      this.schema = copyFrom.schema == null ? null : copyFrom.schema.copy();
192      this.type = copyFrom.type;
193      this.uniqueItems = copyFrom.uniqueItems;
194
195      this.examples = copyOf(copyFrom.examples);
196   }
197
198   /**
199    * Make a deep copy of this object.
200    *
201    * @return A deep copy of this object.
202    */
203   public ParameterInfo copy() {
204      return new ParameterInfo(this);
205   }

228   /**
229    * Copies any non-null fields from the specified object to this object.
230    *
231    * @param p
232    *    The object to copy fields from.
233    *    <br>Can be <jk>null</jk>.
234    * @return This object.
235    */
236   public ParameterInfo copyFrom(ParameterInfo p) {
237      if (p != null) {
238         if (p.name != null)
239            name = p.name;
240         if (p.in != null)
241            in = p.in;
242         if (p.description != null)
243            description = p.description;
244         if (p.type != null)
245            type = p.type;
246         if (p.format != null)
247            format = p.format;
248         if (p.pattern != null)
249            pattern = p.pattern;
250         if (p.collectionFormat != null)
251            collectionFormat = p.collectionFormat;
252         if (p.maximum != null)
253            maximum = p.maximum;
254         if (p.minimum != null)
255            minimum = p.minimum;
256         if (p.multipleOf != null)
257            multipleOf = p.multipleOf;
258         if (p.maxLength != null)
259            maxLength = p.maxLength;
260         if (p.minLength != null)
261            minLength = p.minLength;
262         if (p.maxItems != null)
263            maxItems = p.maxItems;
264         if (p.minItems != null)
265            minItems = p.minItems;
266         if (p.required != null)
267            required = p.required;
268         if (p.allowEmptyValue != null)
269            allowEmptyValue = p.allowEmptyValue;
270         if (p.exclusiveMaximum != null)
271            exclusiveMaximum = p.exclusiveMaximum;
272         if (p.exclusiveMinimum != null)
273            exclusiveMinimum = p.exclusiveMinimum;
274         if (p.uniqueItems != null)
275            uniqueItems = p.uniqueItems;
276         if (p.schema != null)
277            schema = p.schema;
278         if (p.items != null)
279            items = p.items;
280         if (p._default != null)
281            _default = p._default;
282         if (p._enum != null)
283            _enum = p._enum;
284         if (p.example != null)
285            example = p.example;
286         if (p.examples != null)
287            examples = p.examples;
288      }
289      return this;
290   }

338      return collectionFormat;

341   /**
342    * Bean property setter:  <property>collectionFormat</property>.
343    *
344    * <p>
345    * Determines the format of the array if type array is used.
346    *
347    * @param value
348    *    The new value for this property.
349    *    <br>Valid values:
350    *    <ul>
351    *       <li><js>"csv"</js> (default) - comma separated values <c>foo,bar</c>.
352    *       <li><js>"ssv"</js> - space separated values <c>foo bar</c>.
353    *       <li><js>"tsv"</js> - tab separated values <c>foo\tbar</c>.
354    *       <li><js>"pipes"</js> - pipe separated values <c>foo|bar</c>.
355    *       <li><js>"multi"</js> - corresponds to multiple parameter instances instead of multiple values for a single
356    *          instance <c>foo=bar&amp;foo=baz</c>.
357    *          <br>This is valid only for parameters <c>in</c> <js>"query"</js> or <js>"formData"</js>.
358    *    </ul>
359    *    <br>Can be <jk>null</jk> to unset the property.
360    * @return This object.
361    */
362   public ParameterInfo setCollectionFormat(String value) {
363      if (isStrict() && ! contains(value, VALID_COLLECTION_FORMATS))
364         throw new BasicRuntimeException(
365            "Invalid value passed in to setCollectionFormat(String).  Value=''{0}'', valid values={1}",
366            value, Json5.of(VALID_COLLECTION_FORMATS)
367         );
368      collectionFormat = value;
369      return this;
370   }

377    * to control the number of results per page might default to 100 if not supplied by the client in the request.

380    * Unlike JSON Schema this value MUST conform to the defined <c>type</c> for this parameter.

564   /**

566    *
567    * <p>
568    * The location of the parameter.
569    *
570    * @param value
571    *    The new value for this property.
572    *    <br>Valid values:
573    *    <ul>
574    *       <li><js>"query"</js>
575    *       <li><js>"header"</js>
576    *       <li><js>"path"</js>
577    *       <li><js>"formData"</js>
578    *       <li><js>"body"</js>
579    *    </ul>
580    *    <br>Property value is required.
581    *    <br>Can be <jk>null</jk> to unset the property.
582    * @return This object.
583    */
584   public ParameterInfo setIn(String value) {
585      if (isStrict() && ! contains(value, VALID_IN))
586         throw new BasicRuntimeException(
587            "Invalid value passed in to setIn(String).  Value=''{0}'', valid values={1}",
588            value, Json5.of(VALID_IN)
589         );
590      in = value;
591      if ("path".equals(value))
592         required = true;
593      return this;
594   }

1118   /**
1119    * Resolves any <js>"$ref"</js> attributes in this element.
1120    *
1121    * @param swagger The swagger document containing the definitions.
1122    * @param refStack Keeps track of previously-visited references so that we don't cause recursive loops.
1123    * @param maxDepth
1124    *    The maximum depth to resolve references.
1125    *    <br>After that level is reached, <c>$ref</c> references will be left alone.
1126    *    <br>Useful if you have very complex models and you don't want your swagger page to be overly-complex.
1127    * @return
1128    *    This object with references resolved.
1129    *    <br>May or may not be the same object.
1130    */
1131   public ParameterInfo resolveRefs(Swagger swagger, Deque<String> refStack, int maxDepth) {
1132
1133      if (schema != null)
1134         schema = schema.resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
1135
1136      if (items != null)
1137         items = items.resolveRefs(swagger, refStack, maxDepth);
1138
1139      return this;
1140   }
